fehd.ADR_TC: 九龍紅磡黃埔花園第四期地下G14號舖

reviews.text: The food taste are far from the real Taiwan local standard
Love the soup base, very very unique taste

I ordered a beef noodle soup, the soup was very flavourful, though the noodles were too soft and the beef was overcooked. Service wasnt the best in the world either. I won't recommend this restaurant to anyone.

The chicken cutlet, minced pork rice, noodles and even the pork cutlet are quite good. They might have made the taste to suit the locals a bit but still delicious. And the portion of the chicken cutlet rice is huge although we have appreciated more mix and match variety on the menu. Extensive drinks choices of bubble tea and others. The air conditioning can get pretty strong so a light jacket would help. Service here is ok, you don’t get much smiles but not grumpy either. Conveniently located inside the mall linking to the MTR and airport express.
Good.
